    public class Link
extends SailPointObject
implements java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Link>, LinkInterface, EntitlementDataSource
    Class used represent accounts on applications correlated to an identity.

      • setAttribute

        public void setAttribute(java.lang.String name,
                         java.lang.Object value)
        Set the value for the key in the attributes. However, if the value is null, then remove the key from the map. If the key is "iiqDisabled" or "iiqLocked", then always set the corresponding field iiqDisabled or iiqLocked to true or false.
        Parameters:
        name - the key to populate
        value - the value to set for the key

      • sort

        public static void sort(java.util.List<Link> links)
        Given a List sort them in a stable order. We don't define what that order is, as long as it remains the same from release to release. The Link collection implementation changed to a mapped collection in 7.1 and element indexes no longer maintain order of the identity link list. This method is used in unit tests that make XML comparisons to previously captured files.

      • equals

        public boolean equals(java.lang.Object o)
        Description copied from class: SailPointObject
        We override equals so that two objects will compare equal if they have the same database id or unique name, but are different Java objects. This is necessary for Hibernate because caches commonly have to be cleared or objects from one session need to be used to match things loaded in a different session.

        equals in class SailPointObject
